<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>AlloyDB for PostgreSQL on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://xaas-cloud.github.io/genai-toolbox/dev/resources/tools/alloydb/</link><description>Recent content in AlloyDB for PostgreSQL on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://xaas-cloud.github.io/genai-toolbox/dev/resources/tools/alloydb/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>alloydb-create-cluster</title><link>https://xaas-cloud.github.io/genai-toolbox/dev/resources/tools/alloydb/alloydb-create-cluster/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://xaas-cloud.github.io/genai-toolbox/dev/resources/tools/alloydb/alloydb-create-cluster/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about">About&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>The &lt;code>alloydb-create-cluster&lt;/code> tool creates a new AlloyDB for PostgreSQL cluster in a specified project and location. It is compatible with &lt;a href="https://xaas-cloud.github.io/genai-toolbox/dev/resources/sources/alloydb-admin/">alloydb-admin&lt;/a> source.
This tool provisions a cluster with a &lt;strong>private IP address&lt;/strong> within the specified VPC network.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Permissions &amp;amp; APIs Required:&lt;/strong>
